abstract: Government scientists say chlorpyrifos is unsafe. And yet it’s still in use.
snippet: Government scientists say chlorpyrifos is unsafe. And yet it’s still in use.
lead_paragraph: The pesticide known as chlorpyrifos is both clearly dangerous and in very wide use. It is known to pass easily from mother to fetus and has been linked to a wide range of serious medical problems, including impaired development, Parkinson’s disease and some forms of cancer. That’s not entirely surprising. The chemical was originally developed by Nazis during World War II for use as a nerve gas.

abstract: Costa Rica's president on Tuesday requested urgent international aid for refugees in the small Central American nation, which has taken in tens of thousands of people from Nicaragua after a political crisis triggered months of violent protests.
snippet: Costa Rica's president on Tuesday requested urgent international aid for refugees in the small Central American nation, which has taken in tens of thousands of people from Nicaragua after a political crisis triggered months of violent protests.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Costa Rica's president on Tuesday requested urgent international aid for refugees in the small Central American nation, which has taken in tens of thousands of people from Nicaragua after a political crisis triggered months of violent protests.

abstract: My decision comes after careful study of testimony, investigative reports and history.
snippet: My decision comes after careful study of testimony, investigative reports and history.
lead_paragraph: No one enters Congress hoping to impeach the president. But when duty demands it, we have no other choice. Our founders included in the Constitution a provision for impeachment, a provision to be used only in the face of the gravest threats to our democratic republic.

abstract: A coalition of liberal groups that included MoveOn.org and Indivisible organized hundreds of protests across the country.
snippet: A coalition of liberal groups that included MoveOn.org and Indivisible organized hundreds of protests across the country.
lead_paragraph: From Boston Common to the French Quarter in New Orleans, a series of protests reverberated across the country on Tuesday evening to call for President Trump’s removal from office, a prelude to momentous impeachment votes set for Wednesday in the House of Representatives.

abstract: Taiwan is ramping up efforts ahead of a Jan. 11 election to combat fake news and disinformation that the government says China is bombarding the island with to undermine its democracy.

lead_paragraph: TAIPEI — Taiwan is ramping up efforts ahead of a Jan. 11 election to combat fake news and disinformation that the government says China is bombarding the island with to undermine its democracy.

abstract: China's President Xi Jinping begins a three-day visit to the gambling hub of Macau on Wednesday to mark the 20th anniversary of its handover to China, with security tight as protests rock nearby Hong Kong.
snippet: China's President Xi Jinping begins a three-day visit to the gambling hub of Macau on Wednesday to mark the 20th anniversary of its handover to China, with security tight as protests rock nearby Hong Kong.
lead_paragraph: HONG KONG — China's President Xi Jinping begins a three-day visit to the gambling hub of Macau on Wednesday to mark the 20th anniversary of its handover to China, with security tight as protests rock nearby Hong Kong.
headline_main: Chinese Leader Xi Visits Gambling Hub Macau as Nearby Hong Kong Seethes
headline_print_headline: Chinese Leader Xi Visits Gambling Hub Macau as Nearby Hong Kong Seethes

abstract: Some LGBTQ people in Kansas who wanted to raise children born to unmarried partners they couldn't legally marry can be denied contact with the children when the couples split up. An attorney on Tuesday urged the state's highest court to make that far less likely to happen.
snippet: Some LGBTQ people in Kansas who wanted to raise children born to unmarried partners they couldn't legally marry can be denied contact with the children when the couples split up. An attorney on Tuesday urged the state's highest court to make that ...
lead_paragraph: TOPEKA, Kan. — Some LGBTQ people in Kansas who wanted to raise children born to unmarried partners they couldn't legally marry can be denied contact with the children when the couples split up. An attorney on Tuesday urged the state's highest court to make that far less likely to happen.
headline_main: Kansas Court Considers Parental Rights of Ex-LGBTQ Partners
headline_print_headline: Kansas Court Considers Parental Rights of Ex-LGBTQ Partners

abstract: Democratic Representative Elissa Slotkin, co-author of a column that helped launch the impeachment inquiry of President Donald Trump, ended months of uncertainty on Monday by telling voters at a noisy town hall meeting that she will vote for impeachment.
snippet: Democratic Representative Elissa Slotkin, co-author of a column that helped launch the impeachment inquiry of President Donald Trump, ended months of uncertainty on Monday by telling voters at a noisy town hall meeting that she will vote for impea...
lead_paragraph: ROCHESTER, Mich. — Democratic Representative Elissa Slotkin, co-author of a column that helped launch the impeachment inquiry of President Donald Trump, ended months of uncertainty on Monday by telling voters at a noisy town hall meeting that she will vote for impeachment.
headline_main: At Noisy Town Hall, a Vulnerable U.S. Democrat Says 'Yes' to Impeaching Trump
headline_print_headline: At Noisy Town Hall, a Vulnerable U.S. Democrat Says 'Yes' to Impeaching Trump
